LogicalColumn.name: Customer D&B Legal Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This provides the legal name assigned by D&B.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Number Of Children
LogicalColumn.Description: This provides the number of children for each customer.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Legal Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the full name of the customer, as legally required for contracts and documentation.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Family Name
LogicalColumn.Description: For individuals, this is the family name/last name. For organizations that are part of a larger group, this is the group (family) name.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Other Name
LogicalColumn.Description: For individuals, this is the middle (or other) name. For organizations, this is the marketing name.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Preferred Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the customer's preferred name. This is generally a first name for individuals and an acronym or short name for organizations.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Individual Title
LogicalColumn.Description: This is an individual's title. For example Mr., Mrs., or Sir.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Individual Marital State
LogicalColumn.Description: This is an individual's marital state, also known as marital status. Examples include: single, married, divorced, and widowed.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Individual Gender
LogicalColumn.Description: This is an individual's gender. Examples include: Male, Female, and Not Declared.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Phone Number
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the customer's primary phone number.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Alternate Phone Number
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the customer's optional secondary phone number.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Email Address
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the email address of the customer.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Internet Home Page
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the home page of the individual/organization.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Fax Number
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the customer's facsimile number.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Pager Number
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the customer's pager number.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Mobile Number
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the mobile/cellular number of the customer.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Legal Structure
LogicalColumn.Description: A classification that defines the legal structure of the registration of the organization. For example, partnership, corporation, etc.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Legal Structure Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This provides a detailed description of the legal structure of the registration of the organization.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Direct Marketing Flag
LogicalColumn.Description: This flag identifies whether the customer has explicitly requested no direct marketing contacts.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Solicitation Flag
LogicalColumn.Description: This flag defines whether the customer has specifically requested that no marketing material be sent to them or that no illegal contacts are permitted. For example, it is illegal to contact the people in British Virgin Island from the United States.

LogicalColumn.name: Key Id
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is the unique identifier of a dimension or fact entity in its source system. In case of composite keys, the value in this column can consist of concatenated parts.

LogicalColumn.name: Source Id
LogicalColumn.Description: This column is the unique identifier of the source system from which data was extracted. In order to be able to trace the data back to its source, Siebel Systems recommends that you define separate unique source IDs for each of your different source instances.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Key
LogicalColumn.Description: Uniquely identifies the person who purchases the organization's products or services. This is a surrogate key assigned by Siebel Systems. It is used as a primary key.

LogicalColumn.name: Birth Date
LogicalColumn.Description: This is an individual's date of birth. Organizations can also use this to reflect the date of registration.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Number
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the customer number that is unique for each customer.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the name of the customer.

LogicalColumn.name: Alternate Customer Number
LogicalColumn.Description: This is an alternate number assigned to the customer.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Type
LogicalColumn.Description: This code identifies the customer type.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Type Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a detailed description of the customer type.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Category
LogicalColumn.Description: This identifies the category to which the customer belongs.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Category Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a detailed description of the customer category.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer SIC Code
LogicalColumn.Description: This is the Standard Industry Classification for the organization.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer SIC Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This is a detailed description of the Standard Industry Classification code.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Government ID Type
LogicalColumn.Description: This defines whether the government identification type is a Tax ID, Social Security Number, etc.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer Government ID Value
LogicalColumn.Description: This contains the actual ID value, such as the Tax ID, Social Security Number, etc.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer D&B Site Id
LogicalColumn.Description: This provides the site identification assigned by D&B.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer D&B Site Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This provides the site name assigned by D&B.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer D&B Global Id
LogicalColumn.Description: This provides the global identification assigned by D&B.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer D&B Global Name
LogicalColumn.Description: This provides the global name assigned by D&B.

LogicalColumn.name: Customer D&B Legal Id
LogicalColumn.Description: This provides the legal identification assigned by D&B.

LogicalColumn.name: Postal Area
LogicalColumn.Description: The first one or two letters of the postcode (anything before the first number). For instance, if the postcode is PL14 4TE, the Postal Area is 'PL'

LogicalColumn.name: Postal District
LogicalColumn.Description: The first section of the postcode, before the last 3 characters. For instance, if the postcode is PL14 4TE, the Postal District is PL14

LogicalColumn.name: Postal Sector
LogicalColumn.Description: The postcode minus the last two letters. For instance, if the postcode is PL14 4TE, the Postal Sector is PL14 4
